### ============================================
### REQUIREMENTS ASSISTANT API - Endpoints
### ============================================
###
### FLUXO DE EXECUÇÃO SUGERIDO:
### 1. Login Admin (0.2) -> obter adminToken
### 2. Criar RequirementSet (1.1) -> obter setId
### 3. Criar requisito com IA (3.1) -> obter req1Id
### 4. Aprovar requisito (2.4) -> salvar no RAG
### 5. Configurar chatbot (6.1)
### 6. Login User (0.1) -> obter userToken
### 7. Perguntar ao chatbot (7.1)
###
### ============================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@contentType = application/json
@setId = 11ca1ef4-abd2-4273-8a21-daf5ba071e85
@req1Id = 0cfae884-105d-44d2-972b-42220c0ccab7

@projectId = 11ca1ef4-abd2-4273-8a21-daf5ba071e85
# Cole aqui um idToken do Google (obtido no frontend)
@googleIdToken = PASTE_GOOGLE_ID_TOKEN_HERE

# Tokens JWT emitidos pela API
@userToken = PASTE_USER_JWT_HERE
@adminToken = PASTE_ADMIN_JWT_HERE

### ============================================
### 0. AUTH (Google Login)
### ============================================
###
### FLUXO: Faça login primeiro para obter o token JWT.
### Use o userToken para rotas do chatbot (7.x).
### Use o adminToken para requisitos, sets, config do chatbot (1.x, 2.x, 3.x, 6.x).
###

### 0.1 Login USER (acessa apenas rotas do chat)
# @name loginUser
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/user/google
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "idToken": "{{googleIdToken}}"
}

> {%
    if (response.status === 200) {
        client.global.set("userToken", response.body.accessToken);
        client.log("✅ USER token gerado");
    }
%}

### 0.2 Login ADMIN (acessa todo o sistema)
# Requer configurar auth.admin.emails no application.properties
# @name loginAdmin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/admin/google
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "idToken": "{{googleIdToken}}"
}

> {%
    if (response.status === 200) {
        client.global.set("adminToken", response.body.accessToken);
        client.log("✅ ADMIN token gerado");
    }
%}

### ============================================
### 1. REQUIREMENT SETS (Projetos)
### ============================================
###
### FLUXO: Admin cria projetos (RequirementSet).
### Cada projeto agrupa requisitos. Use setId nos próximos passos.
###

### 1.1 Criar um novo projeto
# @name createSet
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/requirement-sets
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "name": "Sistema Legal"
}

> {%
    if (response.status === 201) {
        client.global.set("setId", response.body.id);
        client.log("✅ RequirementSet criado com ID: " + response.body.id);
    }
%}

### 1.2 Listar todos os projetos
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/requirement-sets
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 1.3 Buscar projeto por ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/requirement-sets/{{setId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 1.4 Deletar projeto (cascade: deleta requisitos)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/requirement-sets/{{setId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 1.5 Listar requisitos do projeto (resumo)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/requirement-sets/{{setId}}/requirements
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### ============================================
### 2. REQUIREMENTS (Requisitos)
### ============================================
###
### FLUXO: Admin cria requisitos via IA (3.1), depois aprova (2.4).
### Aprovação salva no RAG para o chatbot e para detecção de conflitos.
###

### 2.1 Buscar requisito por ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/requirements/{{req1Id}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 2.2 Listar requisitos do projeto
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/requirements/set/{{setId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 2.3 Histórico do requisito
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/requirements/{{req1Id}}/history
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 2.4 Aprovar requisito (salva no RAG)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/requirements/{{req1Id}}/approve
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

> {%
    if (response.status === 200) {
        client.log("✅ Requisito aprovado e salvo no RAG!");
    }
%}

### ============================================
### 3. REQUIREMENTS ASSISTANT (IA)
### ============================================
###
### FLUXO: Admin envia texto bruto -> IA refina e salva com status PENDING_APPROVAL.
### Depois use 2.4 para aprovar e incluir no RAG.
### A IA usa contexto dos requisitos já aprovados para detectar conflitos.
###

### 3.1 Criar requisito (processar com IA)
# @name createReq1
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/requirements-assistant
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "requirement": "O usuario deve logar digitalmente, sem senha e apenas digital",
  "requirementSetId": "{{setId}}"
}

> {%
    if (response.status === 201) {
        client.global.set("req1Id", response.body.uuid);
        client.log("✅ Requisito criado pela IA! UUID: " + response.body.uuid);
        client.log("💡 Próximo: aprovar (2.4) para salvar no RAG");
    }
%}

### 3.2 Alternativa: criar via /api/requirements (retorna DTO)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/requirements
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "requirement": "O sistema deve validar email antes de cadastrar",
  "requirementSetId": "{{setId}}"
}

### ============================================
### 4. FLUXO COMPLETO (exemplo)
### ============================================
###
### ORDEM: loginAdmin -> createProject -> createReq -> approve -> configChatbot -> loginUser -> askChatbot
###

### Passo 1: Criar projeto
# @name createProject
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/requirement-sets
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "name": "Projeto Exemplo"
}

> {%
    if (response.status === 201) {
        client.global.set("projectId", response.body.id);
        client.log("📁 Projeto criado: " + response.body.name);
    }
%}

### Passo 2: Criar requisito com IA
# @name createFirstReq
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/requirements-assistant
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "requirement": "O sistema deve permitir cadastro de usuarios com nome, email e telefone",
  "requirementSetId": "{{projectId}}"
}

> {%
    if (response.status === 201) {
        client.global.set("firstReqId", response.body.uuid);
        client.log("📝 Requisito criado: " + response.body.requirementId);
    }
%}

### Passo 3: Aprovar (salva no RAG)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/requirements/{{firstReqId}}/approve
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Passo 4: Segundo requisito (IA usa contexto do primeiro)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/requirements-assistant
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "requirement": "O sistema deve validar se o email ja existe antes de cadastrar",
  "requirementSetId": "{{projectId}}"
}

> {%
    if (response.status === 201) {
        client.global.set("secondReqId", response.body.uuid);
    }
%}

### Passo 5: Configurar chatbot
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/chatbot/config
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "requirementSetId": "{{projectId}}",
  "startTime": "08:00",
  "endTime": "18:00"
}

### Passo 6: Perguntar ao chatbot (user ou admin)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chatbot/ask
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

{
  "question": "Como funciona o cadastro de usuarios?"
}

> {%
    if (response.status === 200) {
        client.log("❓ " + response.body.question);
        client.log("💬 " + response.body.answer);
        client.log("✅ Sucesso: " + response.body.success);
    }
%}

### ============================================
### 5. CHATBOT - ADMIN (Configuração)
### ============================================
###
### FLUXO: Admin configura qual projeto e horário o chatbot usa.
### Apenas uma config ativa por vez.
###

### 6.1 Criar/atualizar config do chatbot
# @name createChatbotConfig
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/chatbot/config
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "requirementSetId": "{{setId}}",
  "startTime": "08:00",
  "endTime": "18:00"
}

> {%
    if (response.status === 201) {
        client.global.set("chatbotConfigId", response.body.id);
        client.log("✅ Config criada! Horário: " + response.body.startTime + "-" + response.body.endTime);
    }
%}

### 6.2 Buscar config ativa
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/chatbot/config/active
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 6.3 Listar todas as configs
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/chatbot/config
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 6.4 Buscar config por ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/chatbot/config/{{chatbotConfigId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 6.5 Ativar/desativar config
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/chatbot/config/{{chatbotConfigId}}/toggle?isActive=true
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 6.6 Deletar config
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/chatbot/config/{{chatbotConfigId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### ============================================
### 6. CHATBOT - USUÁRIO (Perguntas)
### ============================================
###
### FLUXO: User/Admin envia pergunta -> IA responde com base nos requisitos aprovados (RAG).
### Só funciona no horário configurado (ex: 08:00-18:00).
###

### 7.1 Fazer pergunta
# @name askChatbot
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chatbot/ask
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

{
  "question": "Como funciona o login no sistema?"
}

> {%
    if (response.status === 200) {
        client.log("💬 " + response.body.answer);
        client.log("✅ Sucesso: " + response.body.success);
    }
%}

### 7.2 Outra pergunta
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chatbot/ask
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

{
  "question": "Quais são os requisitos de cadastro?"
}

### ============================================
### 7. TESTES DE VALIDAÇÃO
### ============================================

### Nome vazio (deve falhar)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/requirement-sets
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "name": ""
}

### Requisitos inexistentes (404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/requirement-sets/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/requirements/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
